## TL;DR: Lab Grown Round Diamond Facts for {{year}}

- A **lab grown round diamond** is chemically, physically, and optically identical to a mined diamond. GIA certifies them to the same grading standards. The only difference is origin
- **Best value on Blue Nile right now:** D-IF Ideal at **$1,560** — the same GIA clarity grade that costs $7,000–$9,000 in natural. That is a 78–83% saving
- **The Lab Price Floor Effect:** lab diamond prices fell dramatically from 2019 to 2024 but stabilized in late 2025. The years of waiting-for-further-drops are over. Prices are not falling meaningfully from here
- **CVD vs HPHT:** both produce excellent round brilliants. CVD is the dominant process for colorless stones; HPHT can produce D-IF but is more common in the luxury colored diamond market. For a standard round brilliant purchase, both are fine — the grading report is what matters, not the growth method
- **IGI vs GIA:** IGI grades lab-grown diamonds 1–2 grades more generously than GIA. A GIA D-VS1 lab round is equivalent to approximately an IGI E-VVS1 lab round. Always calibrate price expectations to the certifying lab
- **The Resale Cliff:** lab-grown diamonds resell at 10–20% of retail. This is not an investment. It is a wear-only luxury purchase. Natural diamonds resell at 40–50% of retail. Know which purchase you are making

