## The Verdict: Should You Buy a Lab Grown Round Diamond?

**Buy lab-grown if:** you do not place personal weight on natural origin, resale value is not a consideration, and your budget is under $4,000. The savings are real, the quality is identical, and the GIA certification on Blue Nile's lab inventory means you are getting exactly what the report says.

**Buy natural if:** natural origin matters to you, you want the 40–50% resale floor as a safety net, or your budget exceeds $4,000 (at which point natural G-VS1 Excellent rounds become accessible and represent strong long-term value).

The [D-IF Ideal lab round at $1,560](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28023534?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is, objectively, the best dollar-per-quality-unit diamond purchase available on Blue Nile in {{year}}. No natural diamond at any price comes close to D-IF quality at $1,560. If those specifications matter to you and natural origin does not, this is the purchase.

Go in knowing the Resale Cliff. Go in knowing prices have stabilized and waiting accomplishes little. Go in knowing GIA certification is worth seeking over IGI.

Then enjoy a flawless diamond at a price that no generation before yours could have accessed.

